  "text": "In the AEI topology, the corresponding zeo and SAPO materials are H-SSZ-39 and SAPO-18. For H-SSZ-39 a Si/Al ratio of 5.0 (64 Al, 320 Si and 64 protons in the simulated unit cell) is selected, close to that reported for zeolites employed in the MTO and methanol-tohydrocarbons (MTH) processes. 10 For SAPO-18, a content around 9.5% Si (with respect to Si+Al+P) is chosen as the experimental benchmark, [CITATION_1] with 50% of the Si substituted through mechanism I (P → Si, H), and in our case this means 4 Si-islands made of 8 Si atoms each, in a total of 32 Si, 184 Al, 168 P and 16 protons in the simulated unit cell.",
